{{Infobox river | name = Forsån | name_native = | name_native_lang = | name_other = | name_etymology = <!---------------------- IMAGE & MAP --> | image = Forsån vid Forsallén, vinter.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = | map = | map_size = | map_caption = | pushpin_map = | pushpin_map_size = | pushpin_map_caption= <!---------------------- LOCATION --> | subdivision_type1 = Country | subdivision_name1 = [[Sweden]] | subdivision_type2 = | subdivision_name2 = | subdivision_type3 = [[Counties of Sweden|County]] | subdivision_name3 = | subdivision_type4 = | subdivision_name4 = | subdivision_type5 = | subdivision_name5 = <!---------------------- PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS --> | length = {{convert|1.4|km|mi|abbr=on}}<ref name=vattenprogram>{{cite web | title=Forsån | url=http://miljobarometern.stockholm.se/content/docs/vp/faktablad/Faktaunderlag_Forsan.pdf | language=Swedish | accessdate=11 July 2010}}</ref> | width_min = | width_avg = | width_max = | depth_min = | depth_avg = | depth_max = | discharge1_location= | discharge1_min = | discharge1_avg = | discharge1_max = <!---------------------- BASIN FEATURES --> | source1 = [[Magelungen]] | source1_location = | source1_coordinates= | source1_elevation = | mouth = [[Drevviken]] | mouth_location = | mouth_coordinates = | mouth_elevation = | progression = | river_system = | basin_size = {{convert|0.8|km2|abbr=on}}<ref name=vattenprogram /> | tributaries_left = | tributaries_right = | custom_label = | custom_data = | extra = }} '''Forsån''' ([[Swedish language|Swedish]]: "Rapids' Stream") is a [[stream]] in southern [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]]. It is also known as '''Stortorpsån''' and '''Forsen'''.
Leaving lake [[Magelungen]] calmly by a small sandy beach, Forsån's upper reach passes through a furrow blown in the 1860s to lower the level of the lake resulting in the present wide torrents passing through the bedrock. In contrast, the last 500 metres of the course are characterized by flat shores and stagnant, overgrown waters. The stream has a vigorous population of [[signal crayfish]] and is the only winter habitat in Stockholm for [[white-throated dipper]].<ref name="Forsan">Forsån</ref>
== Catchment area == Approximately half of the catchment area is occupied by contaminated ground and polluting operations in the [[Larsboda]] industrial area; with the remaining area composed of parks and green spaces. One of the minor [[allotment (gardening)|allotment-garden]]'s is located in an area which is crossed by two major traffic routes and a railway.<ref name="vattenprogram-30.2">Vattenprogram, p 30.2</ref>
=== Environmental influence === The inflow from Magelungen brings approximately 2 [[Metric ton|tons]] of [[phosphorus]] and 30 tons of [[nitrogen]] to Forsån, the contribution from the catchment area itself, 10&nbsp;kg and 40&nbsp;kg respectively, is insignificant in comparison. No estimates of the level of metals brought to the stream has been done, but low or moderate levels of common metals were reported in river sediments in 1997. Although very high levels of [[lead]] next to the road Magelungsvägen were reported.<ref name="vattenprogram-30.2" />
== Fauna == Samples of bottom fauna taken in 1998 documented the presence of nationally rare species of [[Gastropoda|gastropods]] such as ''[[Hippeutis complanatus]]'' and bivalve [[swan mussel]]; and during the preceding decades two species of [[Limnetic zone|limnetic]] gastropods were documented. Larvae of [[white-legged damselfly]] and [[blue-tailed damselfly]] were recorded in summer 2000. [[Signal crayfish]] and [[trout]] have been introduced in the stream, of which the former succeeded in establishing while [[Rutilus|roach]] is believed to be unfavourable to the latter. The [[white water]] rapids make a section of the stream ice-free during the winter time which attracts [[white-throated dipper]]s and [[common kingfisher]]s. In 1996, traces of [[beaver]] were reported.<ref name="vattenprogram-30.3">Vattenprogram, p 30.3</ref>
