{{Infobox landform | water = | name = Hammond's Knoll | other_name = | photo = Haisboro Sands.jpg | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location map of Hammond's Knoll (right edge of map) <!-- map --> | map = | relief = | map_image = | map_caption = <!-- location --> | location = Southern North Sea | coordinates = {{coord|52|52|N|1|55|E|dim:15000_region:GB-NFK|display=it}} | coordinates_ref = | range = | part_of = | water_bodies = | elevation_ft = <!-- or |elevation_m = --> | elevation_ref = | surface_elevation_ft = <!-- or |surface_elevation_m = --> | surface_elevation_ref = | highest_point = | highest_elevation = | highest_coords = | length = | width = | area = | depth = | drop = | formed_by = | geology = <!-- or |type = --> | age = | orogeny = | volcanic_arc/belt = | volcanic_arc = | volcanic_belt = | volcanic_field = | eruption = | last_eruption = | topo = | operator = | designation = | free_label_1 = | free_data_1 = | free_label_2 = | free_data_2 = | website = | embed = }}'''Hammond's Knoll''' is a {{convert|6|mi|adj=on}} long [[sandbank]] off the coast of [[Norfolk, England]] at [[Happisburgh]], to the east of [[Haisborough Sands]]. The sandbank at low tide has a depth of {{convert|6|fathom|m}} at each end, and {{convert|3|fathom|m}} in the centre. The sandbank has lighted buoys at its north and east ends.
==Ships wrecked on Hammond's Knoll== Some of the ships wrecked here include: <!-- Note to editors: Please either wikilink or provide citations --> *[[HMS Invincible (1765)|HMS ''Invincible'']] - 1801 with the loss of 400 lives. * Galatea - 1898 *[[SS English Trader|SS ''English Trader'']] - 1941<ref>{{cite book | title=The Loss of the English Trader | last=Jolly | first=Cyril | publisher=Acorn Editions | year=1988 | isbn=0-906554-06-3 }}</ref> {{Expand list|date=August 2008}}
