''[[Zootopia]]'' (known as ''Zootropolis'' in some regions)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2016/mar/09/why-are-film-titles-still-being-changed-for-international-release |title=Why are film titles still being changed for international release? |last=Lee |first=Benjamin |date=March 9, 2016 |accessdate=June 6, 2017 |work=[[The Guardian]] |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170417034925/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2016/mar/09/why-are-film-titles-still-being-changed-for-international-release |archivedate=April 17, 2017 }}</ref> is a 2016 American [[3-D film|3D]] [[Computer-animated film|computer-animated]] [[Buddy film|buddy comedy]] film produced by [[Walt Disney Animation Studios]] and released by [[Walt Disney Pictures]]. The film was directed by [[Byron Howard]] and [[Rich Moore]] and was based on a screenplay written by [[Jared Bush]] (who also co-directed) and [[Phil Johnston (filmmaker)|Phil Johnston]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/reviews/zootopia-film-review-1201703504/ |title=Film Review: 'Zootopia' |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=February 12, 2016 |accessdate=June 6, 2017 |last=Debruge |first=Peter |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170613112358/http://variety.com/2016/film/reviews/zootopia-film-review-1201703504/ |archivedate=June 13, 2017 }}</ref> ''Zootopia'' focuses on the unlikely partnership between an ambitious rabbit police officer, Judy Hopps (voiced by [[Ginnifer Goodwin]]) and a crafty red fox con artist, Nick Wilde (voiced by [[Jason Bateman]]) as they uncover a conspiracy behind the mysterious disappearance of predators from a mammalian metropolis.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/mar/27/zootropolis-review-disney-animated-odd-couple-mark-kermode |title=Zootropolis review: Disney's animated odd couple has a perfect chemistry |first=Mark |last=Kermode |work=[[The Observer]] |date=March 27, 2016 |accessdate=December 25, 2016 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224190653/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/mar/27/zootropolis-review-disney-animated-odd-couple-mark-kermode |archivedate=December 24, 2016 }}</ref>

The film premiered on February 11, 2016, in Denmark<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.viva-press.com/release-dates/zootropolis-release-dates/|title=Zootropolis – Release Dates|publisher=Viva Press|accessdate=27 June 2017}}</ref> before going into wide release in more than 3,800 theaters in the United States and Canada on March 4.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=disney2016.htm |title=Zootopia |publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]] |accessdate=June 6, 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170528042942/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=disney2016.htm |archivedate=May 28, 2017 }}</ref> It debuted in first place on its opening weekend earning more than [[United States dollar|$]]75 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2016&wknd=10&p=.htm |title=March 4-6, 2016 |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=June 6, 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170604183644/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/weekend/chart/?yr=2016&wknd=10&p=.htm |archivedate=June 4, 2017 }}</ref> ''Zootopia'' grossed a worldwide total of over $1 billion at the box office on a production budget of $150 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/zootopia-box-office-profits-2016-1202054777/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=March 29, 2017 |accessdate=June 6, 2017 |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |title=No. 5 'Zootopia' Box Office Profits&nbsp;– 2016 Most Valuable Movie Blockbuster Tournament |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518213612/http://deadline.com/2017/03/zootopia-box-office-profits-2016-1202054777/ |archivedate=May 18, 2017 }}</ref> [[Rotten Tomatoes]], a [[review aggregator]] surveyed 256 reviews, and judged 98% to be positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/zootopia/ |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=June 29, 2017 |title=Zootropolis (2016) |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170527214846/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/zootopia |archivedate=May 27, 2017 }}</ref>

''Zootopia'' garnered a variety of awards and nominations, many of them in the Best Animated Feature category. At the [[89th Academy Awards]], the film won [[Academy Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]]. It also won the [[Golden Globe Award for Best Animated Feature Film]] and was nominated for the [[BAFTA Award for Best Animated Film]]. At the [[44th Annie Awards]], ''Zootopia'' received eleven nominations and won six including [[Annie Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]] and Outstanding Achievement, Voice Acting in an Animated Feature Production for Bateman. The film won [[Producers Guild of America Award for Best Animated Motion Picture|Best Animated Motion Picture]] at the [[Producers Guild of America Awards 2016|28th Producers Guild of America Awards]]. Goodwin received the Best Animated Female award from the [[Alliance of Women Film Journalists]] and received nominations from the [[People's Choice Awards]], and the [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association]]. Musician [[Sia (musician)|Sia]] and music producers [[Stargate (music producers)|Stargate]] garnered a nomination for the [[Grammy Award for Best Song Written for Visual Media]] for "[[Try Everything]]". The [[American Film Institute]] included ''Zootopia'' in their list of the top ten of 2016.<ref name=AFI>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/12/afi-awards-film-2016-list-silence-sully-zootopia-1201867080/ |title=AFI Awards: Best Of 2016 Film List Includes 'Silence', 'Hacksaw Ridge' & More |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=December 8, 2016 |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |accessdate=June 6, 2017 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222192150/http://deadline.com/2016/12/afi-awards-film-2016-list-silence-sully-zootopia-1201867080/ |archivedate=December 22, 2016 }}</ref>

